OL,3,GGrampian
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAll parts will have a dry day.
OL,6,FThere will be variable amounts of
OL,7,Fcloud but some sunny spells breaking
OL,8,Fthrough in most places by afternoon.
OL,9,FWarm, especially in the east.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FThis evening will be dry with
OL,12,Fsome late sunshine in places. Then
OL,13,Fmostly dry overnight, perhaps the odd
OL,14,Flight shower across Moray. Freshening
OL,15,Fwesterly breeze.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FA dry day with some hazy
OL,18,Fsunshine developing by the afternoon.
OL,19,FBrisk westerly winds across the west.
OL,20,FPatchy rain spreading southeast in the
OL,21,Fevening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
